for 450g pork mince

sauce:
- 18g soy sauce (1 tbsp)
- 15g dark soy (optional)
- 15g shaoxing wine (1 tbsp)
- 5g sugar (1 tsp)
- 9g pun chun (1.5 tsp chilli garlic sauce)

meat & beans:
- chop ends off beans and cut into bite-sized pieces
- pan to 230°C
- sear beans in 1.5tbsp oil for 2.5 mins, tossing every 30s after 1 min
- pan down to 160°C
- add 1 brown onion, chopped
- then add a few cloves of garlic & 7g ginger, cook for 1 min
- add pork. Cook and break up for 2 min
- add sauce and cook for 30s
- add beans and stir through for 30s



